# Build context exclusions for the fraud-detection Dockerfile.
# Sprint 5 prompt 5.1.g.
#
# Goal: shrink build context from ~1.7 GB (full repo with parquets +
# mlruns + notebook outputs) to <10 MB so `docker build` is fast and
# reproducible. Anything not listed in the Dockerfile's COPY directives
# can be excluded here without functional impact; this file is the
# defence in depth.

# --- VCS + IDE ---
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/
.idea/
.vscode/
.claude/

# --- Python build / cache artefacts ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.eggs/
wheels/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.python-version

# --- Test / lint / type-check caches ---
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pyright/
htmlcov/
.coverage
coverage.xml
.tox/
.hypothesis/
.nbmake/

# --- Secrets / local config (must NEVER ship) ---
.env
*.env
!.env.example
kaggle.json
.kaggle/

# --- Data / runs / scratch (large + irrelevant) ---
data/
logs/
mlruns/
reports/

# --- Notebooks (large outputs + not needed by the API) ---
notebooks/
*.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Sprint reports / docs / tests (not needed in image) ---
sprints/
docs/
tests/

# --- Auxiliary models (Model B/C — Sprint 5.1.f only loads Model A) ---
models/sprint3/fraudnet/
models/sprint3/fraudgnn/

# --- Misc ---
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
Thumbs.db
*.log
*.tmp

# --- Docker / compose (not needed inside the image) ---
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml
docker-compose*.yaml

# --- Top-level markdown except README (which pyproject references) ---
*.md
!README.md
